definitions.definition: Land adjoining a non-flowing body of water, such as an ocean, lake or pond.
examples: lake shore ;  bay shore ;  gulf shore ;  island shore ;  mainland shore ;  river shore ;  estuary shore ;  pond shore ;  sandy shore ;  rocky shore

definitions.definition: ( from the perspective of one on a body of water ) Land, usually near a port.
examples: The seamen were serving on shore instead of in ships.
The passengers signed up for shore tours.

main_definition: Land adjoining a non-flowing body of water, such as an ocean, lake or pond.
secondary_definitions: ( from the perspective of one on a body of water ) Land, usually near a port.

definitions.definition: A prop or strut supporting some structure or weight above it.
examples: The shores stayed upright during the earthquake.

main_definition: A prop or strut supporting some structure or weight above it.
